        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 6:31PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 631 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bottomless Lakes State Park, or 11 miles southeast of Roswell,
moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bottomless Lakes State Park and Bitter Lake Wildlife Refuge.

This includes Highway 380 between Mile Markers 161 and 173.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
